This I ſhall endeavour to make good by Preſidents, by reaſons of Law and State-policy;
beginning with the new making, and then proceeding to the keeping and
ordering of the Seale, during the preſent differences and neceſſity.

2. No originall Writs can be ſued forth without going to Oxford;
which none who holds with the Parliament can doe, without perill of
his life or liberty.
